---
import PageLayout from '@/layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import siteConfig from '@/config/site.config';
---

<PageLayout
  title="About VMFlux"
  description="About VMFlux and its focus on practical Navisworks export workflows."
>
  <section class="border-b border-border bg-background">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-16 lg:px-8">
      <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-brand-600">About</p>
      <h1 class="mt-3 text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-foreground">
        Built for practical export workflows.
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 max-w-3xl text-lg text-foreground-muted">
        VMFlux is focused on professional export tools for Navisworks users who need
        dependable output for visualization, coordination, handoff, and downstream processing.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="border-b border-border bg-muted/30">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-5 lg:px-8">
      <div class="grid gap-4 text-sm font-semibold text-foreground md:grid-cols-3">
        <div>OBJ + MTL available now</div>
        <div>Supports Navisworks 2024 / 2025 / 2026</div>
        <div>GLB / glTF + Properties planned next</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-background">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-16 lg:px-8">
      <div class="space-y-12">
        <section>
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-brand-600">What VMFlux is</p>
          <h2 class="mt-3 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-foreground">
            A focused product line for Navisworks export.
          </h2>
          <div class="mt-6 space-y-4 text-base leading-7 text-foreground-muted">
            <p>
              VMFlux is built around a simple goal: make it easier to move useful model
              data out of Navisworks in a format that downstream workflows can actually use.
            </p>
            <p>
              Instead of trying to be a broad platform, VMFlux focuses on practical,
              production-minded export tools with clear controls, dependable results,
              and support for real project workflows.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section>
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-brand-600">Current focus</p>
          <h2 class="mt-3 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-foreground">
            OBJ + MTL today, broader export coverage next.
          </h2>
          <div class="mt-6 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
            <div class="rounded-3xl border border-border bg-card p-8">
              <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-foreground">Available now</h3>
              <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-7 text-foreground-muted">
                VMFlux OBJ Exporter supports current Navisworks releases and provides
                OBJ + MTL output with material-aware behavior, export scope control,
                and practical units handling.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="rounded-3xl border border-border bg-card p-8">
              <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-foreground">Coming next</h3>
              <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-7 text-foreground-muted">
                VMFlux is expanding toward GLB / glTF and properties export to support
                richer interoperability, modern viewers, and structured downstream workflows.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section>
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-brand-600">Why it exists</p>
          <h2 class="mt-3 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-foreground">
            Built around real project needs.
          </h2>
          <div class="mt-6 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-3">
            <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border bg-card p-6">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">Practical</h3>
              <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-7 text-foreground-muted">
                Features are chosen for workflows that teams actually use, not just for demos.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border bg-card p-6">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">Focused</h3>
              <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-7 text-foreground-muted">
                VMFlux stays focused on making export workflows clearer, cleaner, and more dependable.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border bg-card p-6">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">Expanding</h3>
              <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-7 text-foreground-muted">
                The roadmap grows from today’s exporter into broader format and properties workflows.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section>
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-brand-600">Support</p>
          <h2 class="mt-3 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-foreground">
            Need to get in touch?
          </h2>
          <div class="mt-6 rounded-3xl border border-border bg-card p-8">
            <p class="text-base leading-7 text-foreground-muted">
              Support is currently handled by email.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-6">
              <a
                href={`mailto:${siteConfig.email}`}
                class="text-base font-medium text-foreground hover:underline"
              >
                {siteConfig.email}
              </a>
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</PageLayout>